    {
      "id": "b2e450c067e81f1864d716a4214ff71722ab2c62",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-05-18 02:18:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI could abandon the old ones, but before I do it is worthwhile to mention that you _should_ be able to just push new patches to the old Change-Id. \n\nThe benefit of keeping the old patch Change-Id is that the reviews and comments on the old patch are kept together.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b7d5abbab01cffd2666a6d44c09b6fa7085db6af",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2018-05-30 17:55:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nCan someone explain more about what \"parallel mode\" means?  What is parallel that was not parallel before?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7c7533223f6b78af1dea790f6834ec6e7bb21d01",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 750,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshanx@google.com",
        "username": "jxiong"
      },
      "date": "2018-05-31 18:21:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I could abandon the old ones, but before I do it is worthwhile to\n > mention that you _should_ be able to just push new patches to the\n > old Change-Id.\n > \n > The benefit of keeping the old patch Change-Id is that the reviews\n > and comments on the old patch are kept together.\n\nYes, please continue abandoning old ones. Too many history there in the old patches, let's get a fresh start. Thanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "629e6cd494ff4afb8a1a357ec216eca5cd66a071",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 750,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshanx@google.com",
        "username": "jxiong"
      },
      "date": "2018-05-31 18:23:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Can someone explain more about what \"parallel mode\" means?  What is\n > parallel that was not parallel before?\n\nThe 'parallel' here means to issue I/O to different stripes simultaneously. It's confusing since we have had some other 'parallel I/O' unfortunately. I changed 'parallel' IO to lockless I/O in my patch though",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "643091ddc7d571c790197929d53779001eb0159f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2018-05-31 18:25:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAh, OK.  Thank you.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e13a71638b45afee177c43a8188775fb350ff998",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 377,
        "name": "wc-checkpatch",
        "username": "hpdd-checkpatch",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2018-06-14 05:08:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis change cannot be cherry-picked to master.\nPlease rebase the change locally and upload the rebased commit for review.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
